<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Every week our Holiday Hero Neil Simpson takes an in-depth look at a brilliant holiday topic, doing all the legwork so you don’t have to. This week: Why there’s rarely been a better time to visit the capital.</p>

<p>London is calling if you want a perfect day out or mini-break in the UK. More blockbuster attractions reopen every day, with most displaying the official ‘Good To Go’ stamp to confirm they follow the latest rules on Covid-secure hygiene and social distancing.</p>

<p>Visit now and you can enjoy the capital without the crowds. Usually in August up to 60 per cent of those on Tubes and in museums are tourists. Now they’re conspicuous by their absence.</p>

<p>Capital culture: Tower Bridge’s glass floor, which is 137ft above the River Thames</p>

